<br>
Scott just posted this on druid groves:<br>
<br>
QUOTE--------------<br>
<br>
Tiane wrote:<br>
<br>
&gt; For example, the quoted reason for nerfing MB was <br>
&gt; that &quot;MB Teams were holding epic pieces hostage.&quot; <br>
&gt; Yet not two months ago at a fan faire Scott was <br>
&gt; quoted as saying they had no problem with that, and <br>
&gt; there were no plans to change it on blue servers.<br>
<br>
Hi! I'm Scott. I would respectfully request that if you're going to quote me, the entire quote be used, as opposed to just the first half of it, and would like to clarify some reasoning while I'm here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
TaralonD summarized the primary reason for the Mana Burn change very wel in the the third paragraph of his post, which is also available here (eqlive.station.sony.com/c...?id=5211<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  in the sixth paragraph, if you prefer. <br>
<br>
<br>
Once again, that is the primary reason for the change to Mana Burn. Simply put, we couldn't develop an expansion that had fun high end encounters while this ability was left untouched.<br>
<br>
<br>
A later paragraph in the same update reads: &quot;In addition to the problem described above.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;In addition&quot; is supposed to further clarify that the &quot;Manaburn Team&quot; concept was the secondary reason for the change. As the author of that paragraph, I truly apologise if the meaning was not clear enough. If it was not, that is absolutely my fault.<br>
<br>
<br>
Finally, at the previous Fan Faire, I absolutely did, in the Producers and Developers panel, make the following statement. (Which tends to make more sense when seen in its entirety.)<br>
<br>
&quot;Right now, we have no intention of changing Mana Burn on anything other than potentially Red servers. At the moment, it isn't being a problem. If it proves to be a problem later, we'll address it then.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
The unavoidable truth is: Situations change, and going into Planes of Power, it became a significant content balancing problem.<br>
<br>
<br>
..and that, friend, is why the entire Development Update began with the statement, &quot;Just like everyone else, we're people. People make mistakes,&quot; and ended with an apology.<br>
<br>
To summarize that three page letter into one considerably more brief sentence: <br>
<br>
&quot;We made a mistake in our initial assessment of the skill, and we owe you an apology for that.&quot;<br>
<br>
Which remains the absolute truth. <br>
<br>
Best Regards,<br>
<br>
- Scott Hartsman<br>
Technical Director, EverQuest <br>
<br>
